ill have use of that seat for a different\",\"snippet\":\"ch time your billing period starts (monthly or annual), your count of paid seats will be synchronized so it exactly matches the amount of members present in your workspace.How does\",\"sourceUrls\":[\"https://notion.so/pricing\"],\"issueFlags\":[],\"createdAt\":[2026,6,20,14,20,12,3871400]},{\"id\":9357,\"taskId\":50,\"knowledgeDocumentId\":50,\"competitorName\":\"Notion AI\",\"evidenceId\":\"T0050-COLLECT_SOURCES_01_03-001\",\"documentKey\":\"TASK-50-T0050-COLLECT-SOURCES-01-03-001\",\"retrievalScope\":\"TASK\",\"scopeRefKey\":\"50\",\"knowledgeDomainKey\":null,\"chunkKey\":\"TASK-50-T0050-COLLECT-SOURCES-01-03-001#CHUNK-036\",\"chunkIndex\":35,\"startOffset\":18319,\"endOffset\":18923,\"sourceCategory\":\"AI_DISCOVERED\",\"documentVersion\":1,\"content\":\"not receive credit but instead will still have use of that seat for a different user for the remainder of the billing period.How are paid seats counted?A paid seat can be thought of as a license for one member to use your Notion workspace. Workspace owners can view the total paid seat count for their workspace by going to Settings & members > Billing. Once you have added a paid seat, you will keep it for the duration of your billing period.When your billing cycle renews, either monthly or annually, you will be charged for your plan amount multiplied by the number of members in your workspace, plus\",\"snippet\":\"not receive credit but instead will still have use of that seat for a different user for the remainder of the billing period.How are paid seats counted?A paid seat can be thought o\",\"sourceUrls\":[\"https://notion.so/pricing\"],\"issueFlags\":[],\"createdAt\":[2026,6,20,14,20,12,5452500]},{\"id\":9358,\"taskId\":50,\"knowledgeDocumentId\":50,\"competitorName\":\"Notion AI\",\"evidenceId\":\"T0050-COLLECT_SOURCES_01_03-001\",\"documentKey\":\"TASK-50-T0050-COLLECT-SOURCES-01-03-001\",\"retrievalScope\":\"TASK\",\"scopeRefKey\":\"50\",\"knowledge