re pieces of content you add to a page (e.g. to-do checkboxes, paragraphs, bullet points, etc.).Unlimited collaborative blocksA per file size limit may apply to any file that you upload to a Notion page or database.Unlimited file uploadsConnect to some tools like Slack & Google DriveBasic connectionsThe AI workspace for work that matters.BusinessRecommended$20per member / monthFor growing businesses to streamline teamwork. [Get started](https://www.notion.com/signup?target=plans) Everything in Plus, and:Does work for you. Completes complex, multi-step tasks using context from Notion, your connected apps, and the web.Notion AgentAutomate your meeting notes and follow-ups, no bot neededAI Meeting NotesSearch across connected apps like Slack, Github & moreEnterprise SearchBetaManage employee access at scale with secure single sign-on.SAML SSOCollaborate in Notion databases without giving access to the entire database. Limit access to rows where the collaborator is assigned.Granular database permissionsAdd a verified badge to pages that are up to date. Appears in search results and AI citations.Verify any pageCreate teamspaces that can芒聙聶t be seen or discovered by anyone except those you add. Great for sensitive information like company planning or performance reviews.Private teamspacesVerify ownership of an email domain to access advanced security features including single-sign on.Domain verificationConnect to GitHub, Asana & morePremium connectionsEnterpriseCustom pricingFor organizations to operate with scalability, control, and security. [Contact Sales](https://www.notion.com/contact-sales) Everything in Business, and:When using Notion AI, our LLM providers utilize zero data retention for Enterprise plan workspacesZero data retention with LLM providersAccess the Notion SCIM API to provision and manage users and groups.User provisioning (SCIM)Unlock extra permission controls to prevent certain people from sharing pages externally, disable guests, and set workspace-level rules.Advanced security & controlsAccess a detailed log of security and safety-related activity for your workspace account to identify potential security issues, investigate suspicious behavior, or troubleshoot access.Audit logOur team of Customer Success Managers are experts to help you get the most out of Notion.Customer success managerConnect to SIEM and DLP tools to automatically centralize audit logs & set policies to detect sensitive content in your workspace and trigger automated actions to remediate.Security & Compliance connections (DLP, SIEM)Establish ownership of your company domain and take actions on workspaces that belong to your verified domain (request ownership transfer, delete, claim)Domain managementConnect to even more toolsAdvanced connectionsCustom AgentsAI agents handle repetitive tasks autonomously, so your team doesn芒聙聶t have to. Free to try, then $10 per 1,000 monthly Notion credits.WorkersBetaExtend Notion with custom code to build agent tools, sync external data, and trigger Notion workflows from anywhere. Free to try now. Starts using credits on August 11. [Learn more芒聠聮](https://www.notion.com/help/understand-pricing-for-workers) There芒聙聶s power in a single platform where you can do all your work out of. Notion is that single place.Nick ErdenbergerGTM, OpenAI [Watch video芒聠聮](https://www.notion.com/customers/openai) Plans and featuresFree$0 per seat/month [Sign up](https://www.notion.com/signup) Plus$10 per seat/month [Get started](https://www.notion.com/signup?target=plans) Business$20 per seat/month [Get started](https://www.notion.com/signup?target=plans) Enterprise [Contact us芒聠聮](https://www.notion.com/contact-sales) ContentBlocks are pieces of content you add to a page (e.g. to-do checkboxes, paragraphs, bullet points, etc.). Teams who want to try collaborating in Notion can use the Free Plan with up to certain number of blocks before upgrading.Pages & blocksUnlimited for individualslimited for 2+ membersUnlimitedUnlimitedUnlimitedOn the Free plan, you can upload images, videos and file attachments up to 5MB each. Upgrade to a paid plan for unlimited file uploads with a ~5GB max per file.File uploadsUp to 5 MBUnlimitedUnlimitedUnlimitedRestore your page to a previous version.Page history7 days30 days90 daysUnlimitedAdd a verified badge to pages that are up to date. Appears in search results and AI citations.Verify any pageUse Notion offline on the desktop and mobile app.OfflineChoose pages to download for offline use.Recents and Favorites auto-download for offline use.Recents and Favorites auto-download for offline use.Recents and Favorites auto-download for offline use.Sharing & collaborationGuests are external collaborators outside your organization, such as agencies, partners, contractors, or vendors.External guest limit10Unlimited guestsUnlimited guestsUnlimited guestsCreate dedicated areas for folks to work together, without creating information silos. People can join the teamspaces that interest them, and leave the ones that don芒聙聶t.Teamspaces (open & closed)Create teamspaces that can芒聙聶t be seen or discovered by anyone except those you add. Great for sensitive information like company planning or performance reviews.Teamspaces (private)Create groups of people according to role or department to streamline page & teamspace permissions.Permission groupsOverride teamspace permissions for specific people or groups, giving you even more control over who has view vs. edit access to content.Advanced teamspace permissionsCollaborate in Notion databases without giving access to the entire database. Limit access to rows where the collaborator is assigned.Granular database permissionsNotion AIChat about anything, generate and edit docs, autofill databases, and find answers across your Notion workspace.Notion AI Core (chat, generate, autofill, translate)Limited TrialLimited TrialAutomatically transcribes your meetings, along with a helpful summary.Meeting notesBetaLimited TrialLimited TrialFind quick answers using info across your Notion workspace, and connected tools like Slack, Microsoft Teams, GitHub and more.Jira, Box, OneDrive, Salesforce, and Asana are currently in Beta.Enterprise SearchUses deep reasoning to produce detailed reports using info across your Notion workspace, connected tools, and current info from the web.Research modeBetaLimited TrialLimited TrialWhen using Notion AI, our LLM providers utilize zero data retention for Enterprise plan workspacesData retention30 day retention30 day retention30 day retentionZero data retentionDoes work for you. Completes complex, multi-step tasks using context from Notion, your connected apps, and the web.Notion AgentLimited TrialLimited TrialAI agents handle repetitive tasks autonomously, so your team doesn芒聙聶t have to. Free to try, then $10 per 1,000 credits.Custom AgentsRequires Notion creditsRequires Notion creditsConnected appsConnect multiple Calendars to manage work and time together.Notion CalendarConnect your Gmail for an AI-powered, personalized inbox.Notion MailUses deep reasoning to produce detailed reports using info across your Notion workspace, connected tools, and current info from the web.Notion Mail AILimited TrialLimited TrialDatabase featuresAdd subtasks, and link dependencies.Subtasks and dependenciesAdd unlimited database properties and filters to organize information.Custom properties and filteringVisualize data from databases in different ways (e.g. donut, bar, and line charts).Charts1UnlimitedUnlimitedUnlimitedCapture, organize, and act on responses right inside Notion.FormsBasicCustomCustom+ conditional logicCustom+ conditional logicBring charts, tables, and lists into one dashboard for a unified view of your work.DashboardsDeveloper platformBuild on Notion and deploy Workers with code or coding agents.CLIRun custom code on Notion to extend agents, sync data, and trigger workflows. No infra required.WorkersBetaRequires Notion creditsRequires Notion creditsAPI automations & integrationsBuild bespoke integrations to connect your Notion workspace to internal tools and workflows.Public APISend real-time updates to your integrations when content changes in Notion.WebhooksPaste a link to a GitHub PR, Jira ticket, Figma artboard & more to add a dynamic preview of content in your docs & notes.Embeds and link previewsSend information from Notion to Slack, and vice versa. Or connect to Zapier to create automated workflows with the tools you rely on.Connected propertiesSame as businessAutomatically create pages and new blocks, set status, assignee, and property values, and more.AutomationsBasicbuttons onlyCustomdatabase automationsSame as plusSame as plusSee up-to-date information from Jira, GitHub & Asana, all synced into Notion as a database.1-way database syncsSame as businessWeb publishingPublish an unlimited number of pages to the web.Unlimited published pagesSelect a custom notion.site domain for your published pages.notion.site domains1555Turn on search engine indexing for any Site. Upgrade to a paid plan to customize your title and description metadata.Search engine indexing (SEO)BasicAdvancedAdvancedAdvancedSet a homepage, customize your Site芒聙聶s favicon and share preview, build a custom header bar, and set light or dark mode.Site customizationsConnect a custom domain to your Site and remove Notion branding for $8/month/domain paid annually, or $10/month per domain paid monthly.Custom domains and brandingPay per domainPay per domainPay per domainAdmin & securityCreate a backup of all the pages and content across your workspace.Export entire workspace as HTML, Markdown, & CSVEnable an extra layer of account security with a second method of verification, also known as 2FA or MFA.2-step verificationExport all your content at once as PDFs. Perfect for legal or compliance backups.Export entire workspace as PDFManage employee access at scale with secure single sign-on.SAML single sign-on (SSO)Automatically provision members in and out of your workspace with identity providers like Okta.User provisioning (SCIM)Unlock extra permission controls to prevent certain people from sharing pages externally, disable guests, and set workspace-level rules.Advanced workspace & teamspace security controlsOrganization level controlsOrganization level controlsGet actionable insights about how folks use your Notion workspace, from the most popular pages to overall traffic. Analytics data begins after Enterprise Plan start date.Workspace analyticsDesignate membership admins who can add and remove members from the workspace and groups, but can芒聙聶t access other security & billing settings.Granular admin rolesAccess a detailed log of security and safety-related activity for your workspace account to identify potential security issues, investigate suspicious behavior, or troubleshoot access.Audit logAdmin content search provides Workspace owners visibility into the content of their Notion workspace, letting them filter, search, and troubleshoot permissions.Admin content searchEstablish ownership of your company domain and take actions on workspaces that belong to your verified domain (request ownership transfer, delete, claim)Domain ManagementConsolidate content from multiple workspaces, including users, page content, and permissions, into your main workspace as teamspace(s) that keep their structure.Workspace consolidationCustomManage the users within your domain, including a dashboard where you can get information and make changes.Managed users dashboard & controlsConnect to SIEM and DLP tools to automatically centralize audit logs & set policies to detect sensitive content in your workspace and trigger automated actions to remediate.Security & Compliance connectionsWorkspace members can send guest invite requests to their workspace owners for review when guests are disabled in the workspace.Guest invite requestsControl over when pages are deleted from Trash, and how long they are retained afterward.Custom data retention settingsAdmins can auto-delete AI meeting transcripts on a customizable schedule to meet your data retention policies.AI Meeting Notes transcript deletionSupportWe芒聙聶re always around to help. Just click the ( ? ) button at the bottom left on desktop, or tap 芒聙聹Help & support芒聙聺 if you芒聙聶re on mobile.Priority supportTailored, proactive around-the-clock support offerings for teams with more specialized needs.Premium supportCustomOur team of Customer Success Managers are experts to help you get the most out of Notion.Customer success managerCustomQuestions & answersHow does Notion AI use my data?We follow our standard [data protection practices](https://notion.so/security) to keep your data encrypted and private. Notion AI will not use your data to train our models unless you opt in to a request to share your data.Any information used to power Notion AI will be shared with AI subprocessors for the sole purpose of providing you with the Notion AI features. We specifically have contractual agreements in place with our AI subprocessors that prohibit the use of customer data to train their models. [Learn more about Notion AI security and privacy practices here](https://www.notion.so/help/notion-ai-security-practices) .Where can I find my invoices?Workspace admins can access, view, and download your workspace's invoices by going to Settings & members 芒聠聮 Billing, then scrolling to Invoices. There you can click on \\\\\\\"View invoice\\\\\\\" to see the invoice PDF.What are your accepted payment methods?We currently accept all major credit and debit card brands.What is a block?A block is any single piece of content you add to your page, like a paragraph of text, a to-do item, an image, a code block, an embedded file, etc. Think of your page as being made up of these building blocks. Learn more about blocks [here 芒聠聮](https://www.notion.com/help/what-is-a-block) What happens when I go over the block storage limit on a Free Plan?If you芒聙聶re using a Free Plan workspace by yourself, you芒聙聶ll be able to add as many pages and blocks as you like.If you芒聙聶re using a Free Plan workspace with multiple members, you芒聙聶ll be able to add a limited number of blocks before you have to upgrade. When you reach the limit, you can still read, edit, and organize existing content blocks as usual, but you won芒聙聶t be able to add new content blocks.Do you offer student discounts?The Plus Plan (with a 1-member limit) is free for students and educators. Compared to the Free Plan, you芒聙聶ll be able to add more guests, have access to more version history, and upload larger files.Just sign up with your school email address and you芒聙聶ll immediately gain access to these features. Thousands of school email domains are eligible, not just .edu!For more info & FAQs, [visit the Notion for Education page](https://www.notion.so/help/notion-for-education) .What do the different analytics tiers mean?Basic page analytics (Free and Plus Plans): Includes a list of page viewers as well as a chart displaying views over time.Advanced page analytics (Business Plan): Includes everything above as well as a list of page editors.Workspace analytics (Enterprise Plan): Includes everything above as well as user level analytics, analytics on all pages in your workspace, and search analytics for content in your workspace.How is pricing calculated for the paid plans?If you upgrade your workspace to one of the paid plans, you will be charged a fee per member.Guests are free of charge 芒聙聯 but they can only access individual pages they are invited to. In other words, guests won芒聙聶t be able to see all the team pages under the Teamspaces section in the left sidebar.How do I get charged when I add members to my workspace?When you add a new member to your workspace, they will use an existing paid seat if you have any available in your workspace. If you do not have any existing available paid seats, your count of paid seats will increase by 1. Changes in membership that occur mid-month will create prorated charges based on the amount of time remaining in the billing cycle when the paid seat was added.For every member you delete from your workspace, you will open up 1 available paid seat. This means you have the option to exchange members in your workspace without paying any additional costs, as long as your total billable seat count remains the same.You芒聙聶ll receive an invoice for any charges accrued by changes in membership on your selected payment method, on the day of the month you initially signed up for your subscription.Each time your billing period starts (monthly or annual), your count of paid seats will be synchronized so it exactly matches the amount of members present in your workspace.How does adding and removing members work?Whether you're on a monthly or yearly billing schedule, your account may be charged on a monthly basis if you make changes in membership. If you added members, your account will be charged a prorated amount based on the percentage of the billing cycle left when a user was added. If you removed members, you will not receive credit but instead will still have use of that seat for a different user for the remainder of the billing period.How are paid seats counted?A paid seat can be thought of as a license for one member to use your Notion workspace. Workspace owners can view the total paid seat count for their workspace by going to Settings & members > Billing. Once you have added a paid seat, you will keep it for the duration of your billing period.When your billing cycle renews, either monthly or annually, you will be charged for your plan amount multiplied by the number of members in your workspace, plus any prorated charges for new paid seats added in the past month. Your number of paid seats will be recalculated at each renewal to match the number of members present in the workspace.What happens when I change plans?Upgrading your plan: Your account will be upgraded and charged immediately. The amount due will be reduced based on the percentage of the billing cycle left at the time the plan was changed.Downgrading your plan: Your account will be downgraded at the end of your billing cycle. Learn about how your features may be impacted after a downgrade [here 芒聠聮](https://notion.com/help/plan-downgrade) How do I cancel my paid plan?Your Notion subscription, annual or monthly, will automatically renew until you cancel it. You can cancel your subscription by going to Settings in the left-hand sidebar on a desktop computer, then selecting Billing, then Change plan. After you cancel, you芒聙聶ll still have access to all the paid features until the end of your billing cycle.Learn more about billing in [this article](https://www.notion.com/help/billing) .What happens if my payment fails? Like if my credit card expires?Your account email will be notified after each failed payment. Payments may be retried up to 8 times within the next month. After this, if the payment did not succeed, your workspace will get restricted to limited-access for a period of time before being downgraded to the Free plan.Can I change my payment method?You can change your payment method at any time in your billing settings.How do refunds work?Our refund policy is simple. If you believe you've made a mistake signing up for a paid Notion subscription online or in-app, please contact us inside the app or email [team@makenotion.com](mailto:team@makenotion.com) . We'll be happy to refund you the full amount (not pro-rated) if you downgrade your subscription within three days of signing up for monthly billing, or within 30 days of signing up for annual billing.If you have accidentally added members to your workspace, you can remove those members at any time. If you芒聙聶ve been charged for members who were accidentally added, we're happy to provide a refund of the prorated charges if you reach out within three days of the invoice date (please make sure the additional members have been removed from your workspace when writing in).And if for any reason you're unhappy with Notion, please let us know at [team@makenotion.com](mailto:team@makenotion.com) 芒聙聰 we'd love to hear your feedback, and will be happy to work with you to create the best experience possible.What if I live in a region with a mandatory refund policy?If you live in the European Union, United Kingdom, or another region with a mandatory refund policy, you may be eligible for a monthly subscription refund past 72 hours. For example, customers in the European Union can receive a full refund for a monthly subscription within 14 days of purchase, rather than 72 hours.To request a refund, please contact us inside the app or email [team@makenotion.com](mailto:team@makenotion.com) . If you live in a region with a mandatory refund policy, please let us know and we'll be happy to assist you.Still have more questions? Learn more in our [help center](https://www.notion.com/help/guides) .\\\",\\\"sourceUrls\\\":[\\\"https://notion.so/pricing\\\"],\\\"issueFlags\\\":[],\\\"documentVersion\\\":1,\\\"status\\\":\\\"READY\\\",\\\"failureReason\\\":null,\\\"collectedAt\\\":[2026,6,20,14,20,11,916026500],\\\"createdAt\\\":[2026,6,20,14,20,11,925106400],\\\"updatedAt\\\":[2026,6,20,14,20,12,22547800]},\\\"retrievalChunks\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":9322,\\\"taskId\\\":50,\\\"knowledgeDocumentId\\\":50,\\\"competitorName\\\":\\\"Notion AI\\\",\\\"evidenceId\\\":\\\"T0050-COLLECT_SOURCES_01_03-001\\\",\\\"documentKey\\\":\\\"TASK-50-T0050-COLLECT-SOURCES-01-03-001\\\",\\\"retrievalScope\\\":\\\"TASK\\\",\\\"scopeRefKey\\\":\\\"50\\\",\\\"knowledgeDomainKey\\\":null,\\\"chunkKey\\\":\\\"TASK-50-T0050-COLLECT-SOURCES-01-03-001#CHUNK-001\\\",\\\"chunkIndex\\\":0,\\\"startOffset\\\":0,\\\"endOffset\\\":601,\\\"sourceCategory\\\":\\\"AI_DISCOVERED\\\",\\\"documentVersion\\\":1,\\\"content\\\":\\\"One tool to run your company.Trusted by teams atSelect payment mode:Pay monthlyPay yearlySave up to 20% with yearlyPrice inUSDEssentials for staying organized.Free$0per member / mon